Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:19.99,Episode Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5\pos(636,349.733)\fad(250,0)\b1\c&H030004&\fscx151\fscy156}Hyouka
Dialogue: 9,0:11:23.04,0:11:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifth period today was math class.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:25.88,0:11:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi-sensei is our teacher for that.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:28.00,0:11:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you already know what kind of teacher he is.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:33.84,0:11:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let me explain from the beginning.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:36.50,0:11:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 9,0:11:38.60,0:11:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He arrived pretty much just as the bell chimed.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:42.89,0:11:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right before he entered the classroom, he stopped for a moment and looked at the class name plate.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:49.68,0:11:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything up until that point was fairly normal.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:53.29,0:11:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He started off by writing down a quadratic equation on the blackboard.
Dialogue: 9,0:11:57.86,0:12:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The equation was simple, but he included a restriction on the domain of x.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:05.78,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs80\b1\frz11.6\c&HBBC9C1&\pos(958.4,644.733)}Domain{\b0}
Dialogue: 9,0:12:05.78,0:12:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he singled out Kawasaki-san and told him to draw the range of Y.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:13.03,0:12:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki-san looked obviously confused.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:15.94,0:12:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:17.21,0:12:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We hadn't learned anything about domain restrictions yet.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:22.09,0:12:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki-san said he didn't know how to.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:25.22,0:12:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then Omichi-sensei got mad and began to berate us.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:30.86,0:12:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told Tamura-san, who's quite skilled at math, to answer next.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:34.65,0:12:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he couldn't answer it either.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:37.94,0:12:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point I realized that he had mistaken how far we'd gotten in the textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:44.55,0:12:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Others in the class began to realize too, and it started to get rowdy.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:48.51,0:12:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the teacher got even angrier and yelled at us.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:54.09,0:12:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:55.31,0:12:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was striking the blackboard as he reprimanded us.
Dialogue: 9,0:12:59.29,0:13:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think there were people in the class who could have solved it, but we had all gone silent.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:06.14,0:13:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi-sensei once again singled out Tamura-san and yelled at him.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:12.08,0:13:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I stood up.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:14.52,0:13:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked him to double-check where we were supposed to be in the textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:20.06,0:13:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah yes, that's when I got angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:24.77,0:13:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened after that?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:26.87,0:13:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After he took a look, he muttered "Oh, right," and then apologized.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:33.84,0:13:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told Tamura-san to sit down again, and then class resumed as normal.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:38.25,0:13:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how Omichi is?
Dialogue: 9,0:13:40.87,0:13:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously. I went through a lot of trouble after the midterms because of him.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:46.98,0:13:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had teachers like him in elementary and middle school too.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:50.65,0:13:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like he's a bad teacher or anything.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:52.89,0:13:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you can't blame him for failing your tests.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:56.04,0:13:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better make it up at the end of term.
Dialogue: 9,0:13:57.79,0:13:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 9,0:13:59.21,0:14:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, what do you think?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:04.70,0:14:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there something strange about that story?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:12.66,0:14:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I wanted to ask you was,
Dialogue: 9,0:14:14.83,0:14:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why did he make that mistake in the first place?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:18.74,0:14:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not the type to do that...
Dialogue: 9,0:14:22.49,0:14:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:23.80,0:14:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is pretty strict, but that's because he's strict on himself too.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:28.66,0:14:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then why did he make that mistake?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:31.43,0:14:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I don't get.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:32.68,0:14:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it either.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:35.10,0:14:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:35.92,0:14:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:36.90,0:14:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go look inside his head and find out yourself.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:42.07,0:14:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This would be simple if I could do that.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:44.05,0:14:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Well that's too bad.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:46.35,0:14:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just give up then.
Dialogue: 9,0:14:47.69,0:14:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:49.57,0:14:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help me figure this out!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:51.57,0:14:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 9,0:14:53.26,0:14:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can figure it out if you just think about it a little!
Dialogue: 9,0:14:57.54,0:15:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me the "You can do it if you try!" speech.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:00.54,0:15:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chii-chan, you shouldn't expect too much from him.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:04.50,0:15:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a grasshopper in his previous life.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:06.86,0:15:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-san, you can see people's former incarnations?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:09.47,0:15:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice diversion, Ibara!
Dialogue: 9,0:15:12.00,0:15:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But right now I'm curious about our teacher.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:14.43,0:15:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, she's persistent.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:16.59,0:15:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious! {かっ。。かわええ。。。}
Dialogue: 9,0:15:26.66,0:15:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After class, Omichi-sensei always writes a note in his textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:30.57,0:15:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:32.69,0:15:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To keep track of how far in the curriculum he went that class?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:36.40,0:15:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I think too.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:37.84,0:15:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And before entering a class he always checks the name plate.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:42.53,0:15:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like he's got all his bases covered, so where did his mistake come from?
Dialogue: 9,0:15:47.17,0:15:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing his memos are like "July 1st, class A" on page 15 or something.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:54.57,0:15:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has to contain at least that much in order to know how far he's gone.
Dialogue: 9,0:15:58.70,0:16:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he got the date wrong?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:01.09,0:16:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That might have made him backtrack, but it couldn't have caused him to skip ahead.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:04.65,0:16:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use your brain.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:07.16,0:16:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's true...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:09.75,0:16:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind if I ask something?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:12.03,0:16:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:13.29,0:16:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why you'd get angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:16.43,0:16:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wouldn't want to talk back to a teacher like that.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:21.04,0:16:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why did you?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:22.84,0:16:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was angry, but not because he was yelling at us.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:28.99,0:16:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then was it because there were people who could have answered but didn't?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:32.04,0:16:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:33.46,0:16:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think anyone wanted to stick their neck out in that situation.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:37.64,0:16:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, because other people realized his mistake but didn't say anything?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:41.84,0:16:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 9,0:16:45.40,0:16:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you felt sorry for Tamura, then?
Dialogue: 9,0:16:50.05,0:16:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly felt sorry for him, but I don't think I'd get angry over that.
Dialogue: 9,0:16:55.71,0:17:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}After all, I can understand why he'd yell at students who \Ndidn't seem to remember anything from the previous class.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:03.38,0:17:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what was it that made me angry?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:09.74,0:17:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I find myself hard to understand sometimes.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:13.55,0:17:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:14.87,0:17:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't know enough about Chitanda to know what makes her angry or happy.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:23.39,0:17:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Oreki-san?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:28.33,0:17:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's safe to assume that Omichi was writing down the class' progress in his textbook.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:34.25,0:17:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he was mistaken.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:36.84,0:17:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}The fact that he carried on anyway means that the previous \Npage must have had a note saying he'd already done it.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:44.20,0:17:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your class hadn't been taught domains yet, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:49.48,0:17:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 9,0:17:51.26,0:17:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what if you had?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:55.55,0:17:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 9,0:17:57.47,0:18:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi teaches math every year.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:00.60,0:18:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At some point, last year's 1-A learned it.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:04.32,0:18:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're saying he might have mistaken last year's notes, I'm afraid that's impossible.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:08.56,0:18:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:10.27,0:18:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The teachers get new textbooks every year.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:14.31,0:18:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They need to have the latest revisions to stay consistent with the students, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:18:19.49,0:18:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is using this year's 4th edition.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:23.63,0:18:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 9,0:18:25.49,0:18:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're filled with useless knowledge, as usual.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:28.49,0:18:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a database, after all.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:33.39,0:18:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the possibility that he mixed up the notes he wrote.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:38.45,0:18:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure Chitanda wouldn't accept that answer.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:46.32,0:18:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't get domains, though.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:49.00,0:18:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already hard enough for me to just draw the x and y axes.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:54.18,0:18:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be scary to be singled out by Omichi.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:57.97,0:18:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 9,0:18:59.55,0:19:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1-D has already learned domains?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:02.84,0:19:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we have.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:04.33,0:19:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi's class already did domains, but my class and Chitanda's class haven't yet...
Dialogue: 9,0:19:12.54,0:19:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:15.34,0:19:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That face tells me you've thought of something.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:18.66,0:19:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:20.24,0:19:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:21.18,0:19:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 9,0:19:21.73,0:19:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure that he made a note a page ahead of where you'd gotten to?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:27.51,0:19:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believe so.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:28.89,0:19:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Additionally, the note was written this year, and shows the class' progress.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:34.99,0:19:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:37.04,0:19:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the memo he wrote wasn't, in fact, for your class?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:41.53,0:19:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was actually Satoshi's class' memo?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:45.04,0:19:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My class?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:50.25,0:19:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is in charge of classes A, B, C, and D, right?
Dialogue: 9,0:19:54.85,0:19:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it wasn't A or B, that doesn't mean it has to be class D's.
Dialogue: 9,0:19:59.50,0:20:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, why class D?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:04.10,0:20:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's quite possible he mixed the two up.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:09.51,0:20:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C is clearly nothing like A.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:12.37,0:20:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Are you an idiot?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:15.33,0:20:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A and D aren't anything alike either.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:17.80,0:20:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi teaches math.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:19.99,0:20:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:21.77,0:20:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A math teacher has a much higher chance of mixing up A and D.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:26.45,0:20:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.41,0:20:51.06,Handwriting,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fs35\b0\c&H2B2B2B&\pos(1005.33,650.667)}Oreki Houtarou's writing{\b1}
Dialogue: 9,0:20:29.90,0:20:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say he wrote "July 1st, A" on page 10, and "July 1st, D" on page 15.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:38.08,0:20:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so what?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:40.33,0:20:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could he have mixed those up?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:42.51,0:20:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had mistaken the D for an A, that would explain what happened.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:48.60,0:20:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True, but how?
Dialogue: 9,0:20:51.27,0:20:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A math teacher would have written them like this.
Dialogue: 9,0:20:57.77,0:21:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Lower case A and D!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:00.98,0:21:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:03.63,0:21:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes sense...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:05.16,0:21:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost points on an English test because the teacher couldn't tell the difference in my handwriting.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:10.94,0:21:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you too?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:13.10,0:21:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my case, it was "n" and "h".
Dialogue: 9,0:21:16.31,0:21:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that does seem likely.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:19.72,0:21:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally cleared that up.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:24.56,0:21:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A and D...
Dialogue: 9,0:21:26.26,0:21:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand the mistake now.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:28.46,0:21:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have gone too far in what I said to him.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:33.24,0:21:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was wrong of me.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:38.24,0:21:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you say that?
Dialogue: 9,0:21:39.75,0:21:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi was in the wrong!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:41.33,0:21:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He deserved anything you said to him!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:43.26,0:21:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides—
Dialogue: 9,0:21:44.45,0:21:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:45.83,0:21:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting pretty late. We should head home.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:48.95,0:21:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Fuku-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:51.20,0:21:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:52.64,0:21:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mystery's solved.
Dialogue: 9,0:21:54.45,0:21:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean! Fuku-chan!
Dialogue: 9,0:21:59.17,0:22:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The normally calm Chitanda got angry.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:01.44,0:22:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so she wanted to know why.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:03.95,0:22:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said it's not necessarily bad to get angry, but the truth is, she never wants to.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:12.80,0:22:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Houtarou, Chitanda-san. We should go.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:12.80,0:22:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2}Perhaps Chitanda wanted Omichi to have had his reasons, and \Nwanted to believe that she got angry because of her own mistake.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:15.88,0:22:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ah, right. Let me clean up.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:23.99,0:22:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Chitanda Eru is just that kind of person?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:28.20,0:22:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. What do I know about her?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:35.27,0:22:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I can predict her actions sometimes, I couldn't hope to understand her heart.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:42.25,0:22:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be a deadly sin, just like she was saying.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:46.82,0:22:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pride".
Dialogue: 9,0:22:49.05,0:22:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better watch out.
Dialogue: 9,0:22:52.06,0:22:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even just today, how many times already has Chitanda done or said something unexpected?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:57.41,0:22:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san?
Dialogue: 9,0:22:58.86,0:23:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going home?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:00.79,0:23:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yeah...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:04.65,0:23:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:06.65,0:23:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:09.28,0:23:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems all you do is help me out.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:14.23,0:23:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and it's a hassle.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:20.45,0:23:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:22.56,0:23:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you coming?
Dialogue: 9,0:23:24.62,0:23:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're coming now.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:27.29,0:23:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:35.55,0:23:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll finish tomorrow.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:38.96,0:23:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.73,0:23:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That might be true for you, Mayaka, but just think about it...
Dialogue: 9,0:23:47.78,0:23:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so today, more of my high school life was squandered away.
Dialogue: 9,0:23:52.86,0:23:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I think sloth is more than enough sin for me.
